        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or property damage, park the vehicle on a level surface, set the
                        parking brake and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f019041" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g019051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Grille Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE MOUNTING TABS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER GRILLE MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GRILLE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four grille mounting bolts (Figure 1, Item 3).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove grille by lifting the grille up and outward from the mounting tabs (Figure 1,
                    Item 1). Set the grille aside for re-installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Enlarge the lower grille mounting holes (Figure 1, Item 2) to 0.5 inch diameter.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four well-nuts, from Kit Part Number 8000823R91, into the lower grille mounting
                    holes. The well-nut flange must be flush against the mounting hole surface.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the grille with four new mounting bolts from kit Part Number 8000823R91. Tighten
                    until snug.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
